#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 PREORIA - The Congress of the People has expressed its shock and disappointment over what it calls the unfortunate developments regarding Murunwa Makwarela. Makwarela resigned as Tshwane mayor on Friday in disgrace after it emerged he'd submitted a fake letter to the city manager declaring he was a rehabilitated insolvent. READ: Tshwane mayor Makwarela resigns Cope spokesperson Dennis Bloem says they’re disappointed at the coalition government for not raising the issue earlier. Meanwhile, representatives of the multiparty coalition in Tshwane have laid criminal charges against Makwarela at the Brooklyn Police Station. The DA’s Jacqui Uys says coalition partners are looking into the matter.